OL,6,F"As parents, this one incident has
OL,7,Fdamaged our vision and dreams of how
OL,8,Fwe wanted our son to live his life,
OL,9,Fgiven his disabilities.
OL,11,F"He has been robbed of any opportunity
OL,12,Fto go to professional counselling as
OL,13,Fwe think he feels ashamed or is too
OL,14,Fscared to communicate with new people."
OL,16,FDC Vicky Heys said: "This was a
OL,17,Fdespicable offence committed against a
OL,18,Fvulnerable young man who had no
OL,19,Fcomprehension of what was happening to
OL,20,Fhim.
